    <h4>Description:</h4>
    <p>Rasgulla is a popular Bengali sweet made from chenna (cottage cheese) balls cooked in light sugar syrup. It is soft, spongy, and soaked in syrup, making it a refreshing dessert.</p>

    <h4>Prep Time:</h4>
    <p>‚è±Ô∏è <strong>60 minutes</strong></p>

    <h4>Ingredients:</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>1 liter full-fat milk</li>
        <li>2 tbsp lemon juice or vinegar (to curdle the milk)</li>
        <li>1 cup sugar</li>
        <li>4 cups water</li>
        <li>2-3 cardamom pods (optional)</li>
        <li>Rose water or kewra water (optional, few drops)</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Instructions:</h4>
    <ol>
        <li>Boil milk and curdle it using lemon juice or vinegar.</li>
        <li>Strain using muslin cloth and wash under water to remove sourness.</li>
        <li>Hang the chenna for 30 mins to drain excess water.</li>
        <li>Knead chenna until smooth and soft. Make small smooth balls.</li>
        <li>Boil water with sugar in a wide pan. Add cardamom if using.</li>
        <li>Gently add rasgullas into the boiling syrup. Cover and cook for 15‚Äì20 minutes.</li>
        <li>Let them cool. Add rose water if desired. Chill before serving.</li>
    </ol>
